Politicians have been warned against meddling in the environmental conservation affairs.Western Region Forest Conservation Committee chairman John Baraza said a section of politicians have been using their authority to interfere with the forest conservation effort especially the Kakamega Forest.He ordered forest officers at the grassroots level to arrest anybody sabotaging the environmental conservation efforts.&ldquo;From today arrest anybody interfering with environmental conservation so that the law can take its rightful course,&rdquo; Baraza said.He also cautioned charcoal burners to stop illegal logging, saying they risk being arrested and charged.Baraza also appealed to residents to engage plant trees as an environment conservation measure.He spoke at St Jude Budalang'i Primary School on Friday.Baraza was accompanied by county environmental conservation officer James Were.